      "title": "NAPCS Unionization Research Project — Executive Overview",
      "subtitle": "PLT Strategies Group, Inc. | May 2026",
      "body": "The NAPCS Unionization Research Project is the first systematic, multi-jurisdiction effort to document union organizing activity across the national public charter school sector. Commissioned by PLT Strategies Group and led by Founder & CEO Peri Lynn Turnbull, the project establishes a definitive, continuously-updated intelligence baseline covering 584 charter schools across 19 states and Washington DC — the full NAPCS member and affiliate universe.\n\nThe project answers a question the charter sector has never formally addressed at scale: which charter schools have organized staff, where are campaigns active, and what are the legal, political, and strategic dynamics that determine whether organizing succeeds in each jurisdiction?"
